Sentencas: The performance of La0.4Sr0.6TiO3+/-delta-Y0.2Ce0.8O2-delta (LST-YDC) composite anodes in solid oxide fuel cells significantly improved when 0.5% H2S was present in syngas (40% H-2, 60% CO) or hydrogen.
Titulo: Effect of hydrogen sulfide inclusion in syngas feed on the electrocatalytic activity of LST-YDC composite anodes for high temperature SOFC applications

Sentencas: However, electrochemical impedance spectroscopy measurements at OCV showed that polarization resistance of the cell increased when the concentration of H2S exceeded 0.5%.
Titulo: Effect of hydrogen sulfide inclusion in syngas feed on the electrocatalytic activity of LST-YDC composite anodes for high temperature SOFC applications

Sentencas: Gas chromatographic and mass spectrometric analyses revealed that the rate of electrochemical oxidation of all fuel components improved when H2S was present in the fuel.
Titulo: Effect of hydrogen sulfide inclusion in syngas feed on the electrocatalytic activity of LST-YDC composite anodes for high temperature SOFC applications

Sentencas: Electrochemical stability tests performed under potentiostatic conditions showed that there was no power degradation caused by the presence of H2S in different feeds, and that there was power enhancement when 0.5% H2S was present.
Titulo: Effect of hydrogen sulfide inclusion in syngas feed on the electrocatalytic activity of LST-YDC composite anodes for high temperature SOFC applications
